{"tid":782469,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[廢老末日][廢青福音] 英公共衛生學家: 為了老人家健康 請勿為他們讓座","createTime":"2018-08-16T18:11:00.000Z","updateTime":"2018-08-18T01:03:06.000Z","uid":136116,"like":40,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":14,"replies":[{"pid":"212448e46f5457b3daf6680066de857ae8603978","tid":782469,"uid":136116,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-16T18:11:00.000Z","msg":"獨立報上年嘅新聞 懶得翻譯了<br />\n<br />\nYou may think that offering your seat to someone elderly on public transport is a considerate thing to do, <span style=\"color: red;\">but experts have revealed that doing so could actually hamper their health as they age. </span> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\nIn fact, <span style=\"color: red;\">old people should be encouraged to stand and discouraged from taking it easy in order to keep themselves fit, </span>an Oxford professor claims.<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/touch.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\nSir Muir Gray, clinical adviser to Public Health England, has spoken out to say the elderly should try to walk for ten minutes a day and relatives should encourage to take the stairs instead of a lift or excalator.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We need to be encouraging activity as we age &mdash; not telling people to put their feet up,&rdquo; he told The Sun. &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t get a stairlift for your ageing parents, put in a second banister.<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"font-size: large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">&ldquo;And think twice before giving up your seat on the bus or train to an older person. Standing up is great exercise for them.&rdquo;</span></span><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\nA concerted effort to encourage older people to keep active can <span style=\"color: red;\">help them live more independently and reduce the need for social care,</span> further experts argue in a new report in The British Medical Journal.<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/run.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n<br />\n淨係quote啲main point 冇quote到成篇文 有興趣可以入去睇<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/10.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\nLink: <a href=\"https://www.google.com.hk/amp/s/www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/elderly-people-stop-seat-offers-public-transport-health-expert-a8006641.html%3famp\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com.hk%2Famp%2Fs%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Flife-style%2Fhealth-and-families%2Felderly-people-stop-seat-offers-public-transport-health-expert-a8006641.html%253famp&d=Y02OgwZIxCgM4tfM%2Bk3LO%2BargVTjPUnXFlgjsLUvQ6w%3D&h=a15d1db3\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.google.com.hk/amp/s/www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/elderly-people-stop-seat-offers-public-transport-health-expert-a8006641.html%3famp</a>"},{"pid":"93bd1b7a4a6a92f096e1af175b0fa3ae61fbb520","tid":782469,"uid":67551,"like":9,"dislike":0,"score":9,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-16T18:18:08.000Z","msg":"今次英國研究唔錯"},{"pid":"e135ab03d97556a16b718d08c75493a7a9924654","tid":782469,"uid":136116,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-08-16T18:20:33.000Z","msg":"係咪開錯台 反應比我想像中差<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b74b529aea7c7a16753ce43560dfb7363316a9f3","tid":782469,"uid":182475,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"e135ab03d97556a16b718d08c75493a7a9924654","tid":782469,"uid":136116,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-08-16T18:20:33.000Z","msg":"係咪開錯台 反應比我想像中差<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-16T18:22:34.000Z","msg":"你聽朝起身之後推一推，等大家返公搭車時就可以睇到<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"